You may not participate in this experiment with a screen that is smaller than 9.4 inches tall by 6.6 inches wide. This experiment also requires a very fast internet connection. Display2:
Please set your browser window to 100% by following the instruction below for the browser you are using: 
 -On Chrome, click on the three dots in the top right corner -> On the dropdown menu near the word Zoom, you can use the plus (+) or (-) buttons to adjust the percentage. Make sure it is set to 100%. 
 -On Firefox, click on the three lines in the top right corner -> On the dropdown menu near the word Zoom, you can use the plus (+) or (-) buttons to adjust the percentage. Make sure it is set to 100%. 
 -On Safari, with the webpage open, click on Safari in the top left corner of your computer screen -> Select Preferences -> Click on Websites and then click on Page Zoom -> You will see https://ucmerced.az1.qualtrics.com/ listed as one of the websites for you to configure. Make sure the zoom is set to 100%. 
-On Internet Explorer -> on the View menu -> point to Zoom -> make sure the zoom is already set to 100% -> or you can use the Change Zoom Level to select 100%. 
 Is your window set to 100%?
Inst1b:
Graphs: The blue line shows the energy consumption in wats, and the dashed line is the critical energy threshold for this location. This critical energy threshold indicates when power hits its limit for that location. You will be shown the energy grid consumption for more than one location. Each graph shows energy consumption for one location.

 

Task: Your job is to look at the graphs and answer 360 same multiple choice questions about energy consumption at various locations. To respond to the questions, you would need to pick one of the options below each graph. When you are done with each question, click the next button to continue.
Have you read the instructions above?
